Jacob Lees is a professional rodeo contestant specializing in bareback riding. He hails from Caldwell, Idaho, and has been competing professionally since 2019.

Lees has had a successful career, with notable wins at the NILE ProRodeo in Billings, Montana, the Cinch World’s Toughest Rodeo in Columbus, Ohio, and the Rowell Ranch Rodeo in Hayward, California. He earned his first ever National Finals Rodeo qualification in 2023.

Here you can follow Jacob Lees’ net worth, career earnings, biography, career, achievements, relationship status, and more.

About Jacob Lees

Jacob Lees was born in Caldwell, Idaho. He grew up in a busy household as one of seven children.

Early Career

Lees’s early career saw him honing his skills in bareback riding, a rodeo event that requires a combination of strength, skill, and fearlessness.

He competed in college rodeo while attending West Hills Community College in California and Western Texas College in Snyder, qualifying for the College National Finals Rodeo (CNFR) for both institutions.

In 2021, he finished in fourth place at the CNFR and 33rd place in the Professional Rodeo Cowboys Association (PRCA) standings.

Professional Career

Lees began his Professional Rodeo Cowboys Association (PRCA) career in 2019 and has been competing in major rodeos since then. He has had a successful career with notable wins at the NILE ProRodeo in Billings, Montana, the Rowell Ranch Rodeo in Hayward, California, and the Chief Joseph Days.

In 2023, Lees made significant strides in his career. He started the year strong, sitting 11th in the world bareback riding standings in the early part of the 2023 pro rodeo season.

His biggest payday was a December stop at the Chase Hawks Memorial Rough Stock Rodeo in Billings, Montana, where he placed second and won just over $6,600.

He delivered a clutch performance at the Cinch Playoffs Governor’s Cup, earning $8,750 toward the world standings, which pushed him into the coveted Top 15 in the world standings to qualify for the National Finals Rodeo (NFR).

His major regular season wins included the Chase Hawks Rough Stock Rodeo, the San Antonio Rodeo, the Sheriffs PRCA Rodeo in San Bernardino, California, and the Governor’s Cup Rodeo in Sioux Falls, South Dakota.

Jacob Lees’s Net Worth in 2023

As of 2023, Jacob Lees’ estimated net worth is $1 million.

In the 2023 regular season, Lees made big moves to cinch his first-ever National Finals Rodeo qualification. His regular-season earnings were $117,808, and he started the 2023 NFR in 14th place.

Career Earnings

In the 2023 regular season, Lees earned significant winnings from various rodeos. He won $6,613 at the Chase Hawks Rough Stock Rodeo, $13,500 at the San Antonio Rodeo, $5,147 at the Sheriffs PRCA Rodeo in San Bernardino, California, and $18,750 at the Governor’s Cup Rodeo in Sioux Falls, South Dakota.

Personal Details

Wife

Bareback rider Jacob Lees’ gorgeous wife is Chelsea Carolyn. The couple shares gorgeous pictures on Instagram.

How Old is Jacob Lees?

He is 27 years old as of November 2023.

How tall is he?

He stands at 5 ft 10 inches tall.

What is his nationality?

He is American.

Career Highlights

  • Career earnings: $ 87,458
  • 2022 world standings place: 33rd (BB)
  • 2022 earnings: $27,185

FAQs About Jacob Lees

Jacob Lees is from Caldwell, Idaho.

Lees started his professional rodeo career when he joined the PRCA in 2019.
